definition: the full amount/to fulfill the quota
forehead/horizontal tablet or inscribed board/specified number or amount

sentences.english: I'm very sorry Sir, but our rooms are fully booked for the next week.
sentences.chinese: 很抱歉，本店一直到下星期的房間全都滿額了。

sentences.english: The unused balance of each shipment is not cumulative to the following shipment.
sentences.chinese: 每批貨色所支付的金額，尚未滿額時不得積累利用。

sentences.english: Professional hospitals are all filled up, and private nursing homes don’t have qualified people.
sentences.chinese: 專科醫院滿額了，私人療養院又沒有合格的專業人員。

sentences.english: At last the English Department has its full complement of teachers.
sentences.chinese: 英語系的教師定員終於滿額了。

sentences.english: We've taken on our full complement of new trainees for this year.
sentences.chinese: 我們今年招收的新學員已經滿額了。

sentences.english: The continuation class has already fulfilled its enrolment quota.
We've taken on our full complement of new trainees.
sentences.chinese: 我們招收的新學員已經滿額了。

sentences.english: School fees paid are not refundable, except in the event of full enrollment or cancellation.
sentences.chinese: 除學位已滿額或被取消外，一切已繳學費，概不退還。

winner/lucky guy/person who always gets good breaks
